{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"91b06c54-582a-46fa-8dce-fb38024dd4b3","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote that xUnit is the only one where the skip reason is a **named property** on the test attribute itself rather than a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e9b1d02a-5efe-47a4-ac52-f2a34b0eeba3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":301,"requestId":"7694:1BB519:FFA0:13401:69F2AC3F"},"id":"0231a349-b4ef-464a-8343-67b62292658e","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:11:33.989Z","parentId":"23b9a214-a1c9-4223-8e08-72f0f6944f8b"}
